ADMINISTRATIVE ASSISTANT TO THE RECTOR & PRINCIPAL

​

Education and Qualifications: ​

Bachelor of Arts, State University of Baja California

JENNIFER RAMIREZ

PRESCHOOL

Education and Qualifications: ​

Studied at Imperial Valley College where she is majoring in Early Childhood Development. She has acquired 60 units in early childhood education and currently holds a California teaching permit.

ADRIENNE NEWMAN

KINDERGARTEN

Education and Qualifications:

Ms. Newman will be remaining with us and will be returning to teach Kindergarten. Ms. Newman came to us a few years ago from St. Gregory the Great School in San Diego. She was a founding member of the school and taught the kindergarten class. She is a graduate of CSU San Marcos and has her teaching credential. We are grateful to have Ms. Newman here at our school and our community.

CAREESA LANDRUM

FIRST GRADE

Education and Qualifications:

​

ALICIA CALLES

SECOND GRADE

Education and Qualifications: ​

Ms. Calles is our 2nd Grade teacher. She is a graduate of San Diego State University and holds a degree in Early Childhood Education. She spent part of her studies abroad in England sharing in an excellent education program at Keele University. She is also qualified in special education and in studies related to autism.

NYDIA GARCIA

THIRD GRADE

​

Education and Qualifications: ​​

Education and Qualifications: ​

Ms. Garcia is well-qualified in child development and adolescent behavior and holds degrees in this area from Imperial Valley College and Union Institute and University.

KEVIN RODRIGUEZ

FOURTH GRADE

Education and Qualifications:

Mr. Rodriguez will join us and take responsibility for Fourth Grade. He holds a Master’s Degree from Methodist Theological School in Ohio, as well as furthering his education at the Pontifical College Josephinum, in Columbus, Ohio, and at California State University, Monterey Bay. He holds many awards and prizes from the educational institutions with which he has been involved and has a particular interest in Catholic Education. We are happy to welcome him to St. Mary’s.

GONZALO ESTRADA

FIFTH GRADE

Education and Qualifications: ​​

Mr. Estrada will be joining our Faculty this year, and will take responsibility for our Fifth Grade class. Mr. Estrada studied for a BA in Liberal studies at Fresno State University. He holds a multiple subject credential and has a wide experience of education in the Imperial Valley. He last taught at Imagine School and held many positions of responsibility there. We wish him a warm welcome.

MARCIA VALENZUELA

SIXTH GRADE

Education and Qualifications:

Mrs. Valenzuela holds a Bachelor’s Degree in Spanish with a minor in history from SDSU. She has a Master’s degree in Teaching and Learning. She holds a single subject California credential and has a specialization in English Language Learners. Mrs. Valenzuela also has extensive teaching experience gained in the Imperial Valley.

MARCOS PACHECO

SEVENTH GRADE ENGLISH AND LANGUAGE ARTS

Education and Qualifications:

Comes to us from Sacred Heart School, Brawley. Those who attend Our Lady of Guadalupe in Calexico will recognize him from helping out at services there. He studied Liberal Studies at San Diego State University. Both of his parents are teachers and other members of his family are also involved in education. Mr. Pacheco will be responsible for 7th Grade and will teach English and Language Arts.

CECILIA TERÁN

SIXTH - EIGHTH MATH AND SCIENCE AND

EIGHTH GRADE HOMEROOM

VICE PRINCIPAL FOR INSTRUCTION

Education and Qualifications:

​Masters Degree in Education; Bachelor of Arts Degree in Spanish with Distinction (Minor in English); Associate of Science Degree in Mathematics (with Honors); Procedure Professionals Association (PPA) Writer Certification, Global Procedures Association

EIRAM ISLAS

LEARNING CENTER COORDINATOR AND
